President Biden and President Herzog of Israel met in the Oval Office to discuss various issues. President Biden thanked President Herzog for his hospitality during his visit to Israel and expressed his pride in receiving the Israeli Presidential Medal of Freedom. They also discussed the historic breakthrough of Israel and Lebanon signing an agreement to establish a permanent maritime boundary, which will create economic opportunities and enhance stability and security for both countries. President Biden emphasized the strong commitment the United States has to Israel based on shared values and interests. President Herzog expressed gratitude for the friendship between the two nations and highlighted the challenges posed by Iran's repression of its citizens and its pursuit of nuclear weapons. They also discussed Israel's integration in the region and cooperation on climate change. Both leaders acknowledged that their friendship transcends political differences and expressed a commitment to working together for the wellbeing of their countries and the world.